<HEADLINE>
FT  14 DEC 93 / Andorra set for coalition
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ANDORRA LA VELLA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Andorra, the tiny principality on the Franco-Spanish border, emerged
yesterday from its first constitution-based election after more than 700
years of feudalism on course for a coalition government, Reuter reports from
Andorra la Vella.
The centre-right Agrupament Nacional Democratic party of the outgoing head
of government, Mr Oscar Ribas Reig, won the largest share of the vote. He
expressed confidence in being able to pursue reform with a coalition
government.
