<HEADLINE>
FT  14 DEC 93 / Peter Boross named to succeed Hungarian premier
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NICHOLAS DENTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The Hungarian Democratic Forum, Hungary's governing conservative party, last
night named Mr Peter Boross, interior minister, to succeed Mr Jozsef Antall,
the late premier, Nicholas Denton reports. Mr Boross won the nomination by a
surprisingly comfortable margin and it now remains for President Arpad Goncz
to formally propose him for premiership and parliament to approve the
choice.
Political continuity is indicated by the fact that Mr Boross, aged 65 and
formerly an executive at a catering company, came to high political office
under the sponsorship of Mr Antall. But the nominee's blunt rhetoric places
him to the right of his predecessor.
</TEXT>
