</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LUCIA VAN DER POST
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
There is hardly a fashion editor who doesn't own a Georgina von Etzdorf
scarf - but there are alternatives.
Calver &amp; Wilson, for instance, go in for rich plain velvets, the most
delectable in panne velvet. The scarves feature richly contrasting or toning
borders. The range starts at Pounds 39.50, with children's versions at
Pounds 12.
The range is stocked at Browns of South Molton Street, London W1, Harrods of
Knightsbridge, London SW1, Joseph, Liberty and other quality shops.
