<HEADLINE>
FT  11 DEC 93 / Briefcase Q&amp;A: Pension payments
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
I am self-employed and subscribe to a personal pension plan. I also claim
capital allowance on my tax.
Is the maximum contribution that I can pay to my pension plan based on my
gross earnings before or after capital allowances?
It is based on your earnings after deducting capital allowances (by virtue
of sections 640(1) and 646(2)(d) of the Income and Corporation Taxes Act
1988). Ask your tax office for the free pamphlet IR78 (Personal pensions: a
guide for tax).
No legal responsibility can be accepted by the Financial Times for the
answers given in these columns. All enquiries will be answered by post as
soon as possible.
</TEXT>
