<HEADLINE>
FT  11 DEC 93 / UK Company News: Villiers
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Including a Pounds 2.08m provision for the loss on sale of the company's oil
interests at Somerset field, Villiers Group, the USM-quoted oil and gas
exploration concern, suffered increased losses of Pounds 2.83m for the year
to July 31, against Pounds 165,543.
Turnover from continuing operations amounted to Pounds 1.87m (Pounds 1.39m)
while there was a gross profit of Pounds 704,081 (Pounds 675,255).
Losses per share were well up at 5.85p against 0.32p.
</TEXT>
