<HEADLINE>
FT  11 DEC 93 / UK Company News: Widney
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A return to profit in the second half left Widney, a maker of windows and
water treatment, power transmission and electronic equipment, with a reduced
loss of Pounds 150,000 for the year to October 2.
The improvement, from a Pounds 371,000 deficit previously, was achieved on
sales of Pounds 22m (Pounds 19.3m). The sales figure included a Pounds 1.16m
contribution from SPC International, acquired in August.
Mr David Cassidy, chairman and chief executive, said the group would have
reported a small profit were it not for the effects of receivership at two
customers - Leyland Daf and Swan Hunter.
Interests costs were reduced to Pounds 546,000 (Pounds 823,000) aided by
lower interest rates and reduced borrowings. The period ended with gearing
of 60 per cent (277 per cent).
Losses per share were halved to 0.49p.
</TEXT>
