<HEADLINE>
FT  11 DEC 93 / UK Company News: Albrighton
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Albrighton, the USM-quoted quarrying concern, yesterday announced a return
to the black and is restoring its dividend after a three year absence, with
an interim of 0.1p.
With turnover up from Pounds 1.16m to Pounds 1.74m, the restructured group
turned round from a Pounds 62,000 loss to a pre-tax profit of Pounds 324,000
in the six months to September 30.
Mr Humphrey Wood, chairman, said that in the last two months there had been
a significant increase in the value of orders received and as a result, a
much higher level of sales would be achieved in the second half.
Share of associate's losses was Pounds 29,000 (Pounds 4,000 profits).
Interest charges fell to Pounds 73,000 (Pounds 186,000). Earnings per share
came to 0.6p (1p losses).
</TEXT>
